I"[<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brains-are-like-stadiums">Neuroimaging</a> consists of measuring <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-activity-is-like-airflow">neural dynamics</a> to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/forecasting-framing-renders-neural-emulation-feasible">identify underlying mechanisms</a>. Similarly, in AI <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/explicit-language-of-mental-states-informs-psycholinguistic-manifold-alignment">alignment</a>, interpretable techniques are proposed to make sense of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/recurrent-networks-approximate-dynamical-systems">complex NNs</a>. Correlating a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cluster-index-quantifies-internal-external-connectivity">neuron cluster</a> with specific <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/multi-modal-mappings-generate-multi-modal-receptive-fields">types of information being processed</a> resembles finding neural correlates through techniques like <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brains-are-like-orchestras">EEG or fMRI</a>.</p>
